had some free time, uh... where you didn't have to

44:11.903 --> 44:40.611
work or didn't have to study what did y'all do for 
fun for to relax

44:11.903 --> 44:40.611
i suspect we we there were two or three of us that 
that on sunday afternoon would go down into the

44:11.903 --> 44:40.611
woods and look for pecan trees and we found hickory 
nut trees down there most of us Spent our

44:41.249 --> 44:48.398
afternoons, well, visiting and so forth. I don't 
remember it. Other than football, I don't

44:49.999 --> 44:53.744
remember that we played anything. Any other game, 
we played football quite a lot when the weather was

44:54.325 --> 44:57.769
good. Did y'all go to the movie much? Not very 
often. After walking to school and back, Every day

45:05.954 --> 45:09.578
we didn't want to walk over there at night. Did you, 
in Aggie lingo, did you all sack out in the

45:09.598 --> 45:14.043
afternoon? Not really. We either were going to 
school or working. All right. So you got up, ate

45:22.052 --> 45:27.118
breakfast, went to class, came back to eat lunch. 
Right. And then went back to the campus. Right. So

45:30.441 --> 45:33.885
you went to and from the campus every, at least 
twice a day. Right. And we didn't walk over to the

45:37.394 --> 45:43.502
campus very often at night, I'll tell you that. Did 
you study in your room? Yes, sir. Who had a radio in

45:48.229 --> 45:49.771
those days? Nobody. And by the way, we studied by 
Aladdin lamps. There was no electricity. What

45:58.203 --> 45:59.805
kind of stove did she have? That's an interesting 
story. We Russell found some old stoves that had

46:04.966 --> 46:12.254
been used years before and stored somewhere. And 
each room had a chimney in it. And we had wood stoves

46:17.499 --> 46:20.602
in each room. And

46:22.384 --> 46:33.876
sometime in the changeover from wood to coal down 
at the electric plant, they had covered up a lot of

46:36.269 --> 46:43.275
wood that had been there for years. And so we mined 
that wood from the covered up place at the back of

46:44.136 --> 46:54.825
the power plant. Did she cook on a wood stove, 
though? Yes, she did. Oh, really? Yes, sir. Oh, my.

